WEBVTT

1
00:01:37.055 --> 00:01:38.241
Yes?

2
00:01:38.265 --> 00:01:41.727
<i>I think you dropped this
money outside the building.</i>

3
00:01:45.898 --> 00:01:48.042
<i>If I'm mistaken. I apologize.</i>

4
00:01:48.066 --> 00:01:49.669
No. please.

5
00:01:49.693 --> 00:01:50.903
<i>Okay.</i>

6
00:02:17.554 --> 00:02:20.825
Mister. Yes. that's mine.

7
00:02:20.849 --> 00:02:22.243
You speak English.

8
00:02:22.267 --> 00:02:23.852
It's part of my job.

9
00:02:25.020 --> 00:02:27.064
It's a lot of money. I'd
hate to see you lose it.

10
00:02:28.565 --> 00:02:29.650
Yes. thank you.

11
00:02:34.696 --> 00:02:37.449
I suppose I should
offer you a reward?

12
00:02:37.950 --> 00:02:39.368
No. there's no need for that.

13
00:02:40.494 --> 00:02:41.912
But I will ask a favor.

14
00:02:43.497 --> 00:02:45.165
I was wondering. have
you seen this boy?

15
00:02:45.749 --> 00:02:48.210
He's been missing for six
days. His name's Yuma.

16
00:02:49.002 --> 00:02:50.420
I've never seen him before.

17
00:03:00.681 --> 00:03:03.475
I don't think you're
being truthful. Hideo.

18
00:03:07.938 --> 00:03:09.940
I think you've made
a terrible mistake.

19
00:03:13.694 --> 00:03:15.863
You sent the ransom
note to Yuma's parents.

20
00:03:17.281 --> 00:03:20.742
The Kobayashis. But Mr. Kobayashi
is not Yuma's father.

21
00:03:25.998 --> 00:03:26.999
No.

22
00:03:27.708 --> 00:03:29.293
He thinks he is. but he isn't.

23
00:03:30.711 --> 00:03:32.814
Yuma's father. his real father.

24
00:03:32.838 --> 00:03:36.758
is a man by the name of Masaki
Hashimoto. and Mr. Hashimoto

25
00:03:38.760 --> 00:03:41.263
is a boss with the Tokyo yakuza.

26
00:03:42.097 --> 00:03:43.682
So the only question is.

27
00:03:44.641 --> 00:03:46.143
what happens next?

28
00:03:48.061 --> 00:03:51.499
I'm gonna give you a chance. All you
have to do is take me to the boy.

29
00:03:51.523 --> 00:03:53.358
As soon as I have Yuma.

30
00:03:53.859 --> 00:03:56.838
I'll give you two hours
before I contact his father.

31
00:03:56.862 --> 00:03:59.841
In that time. you go to the airport.
you buy a ticket somewhere. anywhere.

32
00:03:59.865 --> 00:04:01.575
as long as it's a
foreign country.

33
00:04:02.951 --> 00:04:05.204
You'll never be safe in Japan.

34
00:04:12.794 --> 00:04:14.213
I don't like hurting people.

35
00:04:14.838 --> 00:04:15.839
I really don't.

36
00:04:17.341 --> 00:04:20.135
Just tell me where you're hiding
the boy. and the deal still stands.

37
00:04:21.720 --> 00:04:24.556
Please. Tell me where
you're hiding the boy.

38
00:04:29.728 --> 00:04:32.064
I'm sorry. You brought
this on yourself.

39
00:04:43.617 --> 00:04:46.161
Goddamn Savile Row suit.

40
00:05:10.686 --> 00:05:12.455
Who are you?

41
00:05:12.479 --> 00:05:14.481
Sit.

42
00:05:42.593 --> 00:05:43.677
Yuma.

43
00:05:52.102 --> 00:05:54.289
Thank you.

44
00:05:54.313 --> 00:05:56.791
It was an honor to be
of service to you. sir.

45
00:05:56.815 --> 00:05:58.168
You're hurt.

46
00:05:58.192 --> 00:06:00.461
- I'll take care of it.
- As you wish.

47
00:06:00.485 --> 00:06:02.321
Wait outside.

48
00:06:09.620 --> 00:06:11.413
I think it's best you leave now.

49
00:06:31.016 --> 00:06:33.101
<i>I don't like hurting
people. It's true.</i>

50
00:06:34.561 --> 00:06:37.940
<i>This world has more than enough suffering
without extra contributions from me.</i>

51
00:06:41.610 --> 00:06:43.320
<i>Finding people that are lost.</i>

52
00:06:44.154 --> 00:06:46.114
<i>Bringing them back to
those that miss them.</i>

53
00:06:47.950 --> 00:06:49.409
<i>That part of the job I like.</i>

54
00:06:51.328 --> 00:06:53.997
<i>It makes the occasional knife
fight and ruined suit worthwhile.</i>

55
00:06:56.458 --> 00:06:57.584
<i>It's tough business.</i>

56
00:06:58.961 --> 00:06:59.962
<i>But steady.</i>

57
00:09:16.974 --> 00:09:20.995
Hopefully. the fever will
break. Did the vomit stop?

58
00:09:21.019 --> 00:09:23.873
I have a client.

59
00:09:23.897 --> 00:09:26.441
so I have to go.

60
00:09:28.652 --> 00:09:30.713
Is the temperature all
right for you. sir?

61
00:09:30.737 --> 00:09:32.507
I can turn up the
AC if you like.

62
00:09:32.531 --> 00:09:34.884
I'm very comfortable. Thank you.

63
00:09:34.908 --> 00:09:35.969
You speak Arabic?

64
00:09:35.993 --> 00:09:38.763
I do. Many years ago. I
spent time in Damascus.

65
00:09:38.787 --> 00:09:41.266
When it was a great city...
before all the trouble.

66
00:09:41.290 --> 00:09:42.851
I am from Damascus!

67
00:09:42.875 --> 00:09:44.602
What is your name. my friend?

68
00:09:44.626 --> 00:09:46.670
Munzer.

69
00:09:47.296 --> 00:09:48.672
Munzer.

70
00:10:11.528 --> 00:10:12.613
Munzer.

71
00:10:13.530 --> 00:10:15.949
I heard you talk
about your daughter.

72
00:10:17.117 --> 00:10:18.535
This is my doctor's number.

73
00:10:19.870 --> 00:10:21.097
Just call him. right?

74
00:10:21.121 --> 00:10:23.892
Tell him about your daughter.
she's sick. and make sure

75
00:10:23.916 --> 00:10:25.956
to let him know that I told
you to call. He'll help.

76
00:10:26.752 --> 00:10:29.189
Blessings to you.
sir. Praise God.

77
00:10:29.213 --> 00:10:30.506
Of course.

78
00:10:31.507 --> 00:10:33.443
- I will wait for you?
- No. No need.

79
00:10:33.467 --> 00:10:35.945
But if you wouldn't mind taking my
bags to the hotel. I'd appreciate it.

80
00:10:35.969 --> 00:10:39.866
And if your dispatcher asks. just
say you dropped me there as well.

81
00:10:39.890 --> 00:10:40.974
As you wish.

82
00:11:11.755 --> 00:11:14.359
- John Sugar. in the flesh.
- Hey. Ruby.

83
00:11:14.383 --> 00:11:17.779
Hey. Come here.
It's been a while.

84
00:11:17.803 --> 00:11:19.805
- Yeah.
- All right. let me look at you.

85
00:11:22.182 --> 00:11:24.410
- You look tired.
- Long trip.

86
00:11:24.434 --> 00:11:26.103
I ran into an old
friend in Tokyo.

87
00:11:26.854 --> 00:11:29.022
He said his local
cell had disbanded

88
00:11:29.857 --> 00:11:32.168
and he hasn't seen the other
members in over a year.

89
00:11:32.192 --> 00:11:36.673
I told him he'd be welcome here
with us. if he wanted to relocate.

90
00:11:36.697 --> 00:11:39.968
Yeah. of course. All right. I
have some things for you inside.

91
00:11:39.992 --> 00:11:41.326
- Lead the way.
- All right.

92
00:11:44.663 --> 00:11:46.808
Mirembe. Mirembe. Mirembe.

93
00:11:46.832 --> 00:11:47.916
Hi.

94
00:11:52.171 --> 00:11:54.607
I didn't know you were
so easily seduced.

95
00:11:54.631 --> 00:11:57.050
It's not seduction 'cause I
know what she's trying to do.

96
00:11:58.302 --> 00:11:59.303
Good girl.

97
00:12:02.264 --> 00:12:04.159
- What have you got?
- From Helen.

98
00:12:04.183 --> 00:12:07.078
- That's sweet of her.
- Yeah. I can't believe she still writes.

99
00:12:07.102 --> 00:12:08.454
Like. she actually writes.

100
00:12:08.478 --> 00:12:09.581
She's old-school.

101
00:12:09.605 --> 00:12:11.624
- She is old-school.
- Thank you.

102
00:12:11.648 --> 00:12:12.816
You're welcome.

103
00:12:14.234 --> 00:12:18.447
So. your flight got in.
what. four hours ago?

104
00:12:19.239 --> 00:12:20.574
Give or take. Uh-huh.

105
00:12:23.911 --> 00:12:25.078
Where have you been?

106
00:12:26.705 --> 00:12:27.706
I had some things to do.

107
00:12:32.127 --> 00:12:33.295
<i>Things?</i>

108
00:12:33.962 --> 00:12:35.315
Things.

109
00:12:35.339 --> 00:12:37.442
<i>Things like?</i>

110
00:12:37.466 --> 00:12:38.675
<i>Things like things.</i>

111
00:12:39.635 --> 00:12:40.928
Things like Jonathan Siegel?

112
00:12:43.680 --> 00:12:45.450
Thomas Kinzie.
Mr. Siegel's attorney.

113
00:12:45.474 --> 00:12:46.534
John Sugar.

114
00:12:46.558 --> 00:12:48.036
Welcome. He's in the garden.

115
00:12:48.060 --> 00:12:50.246
<i>- You spying on me again?
- No. I...</i>

116
00:12:50.270 --> 00:12:53.333
I just got a call
from Thomas Kinzie.

117
00:12:53.357 --> 00:12:55.335
Yeah. about your contract.

118
00:12:55.359 --> 00:12:59.422
which I thought was really strange
because when he called me three days ago.

119
00:12:59.446 --> 00:13:03.408
I told him very clearly
that you were unavailable.

120
00:13:05.327 --> 00:13:06.304
Maybe.

121
00:13:06.328 --> 00:13:08.413
I contacted the
references you provided.

122
00:13:08.997 --> 00:13:11.017
They all said you're a
man of great integrity.

123
00:13:11.041 --> 00:13:12.435
When it comes to his family.

124
00:13:12.459 --> 00:13:15.730
Mr. Siegel is an
incredibly private person.

125
00:13:15.754 --> 00:13:18.858
Any public knowledge of
this very personal concern

126
00:13:18.882 --> 00:13:20.968
would be greatly
distressing for him.

127
00:13:21.552 --> 00:13:23.887
- There he is.
- There he is.

128
00:13:26.098 --> 00:13:28.660
Plant as many as you can. But
get some more soil in here.

129
00:13:28.684 --> 00:13:30.804
That'll be all. Thank you.
Thank you. I appreciate it.

130
00:13:32.312 --> 00:13:35.500
Sugar. Jonathan Siegel.

131
00:13:35.524 --> 00:13:37.919
It's an honor to meet you. sir.
I'm a great admirer of your work.

132
00:13:37.943 --> 00:13:41.130
Though I have seen every
movie you've ever produced.

133
00:13:41.154 --> 00:13:43.466
Most. at least
five or six times.

134
00:13:43.490 --> 00:13:45.510
except <i>Lady In The Shadows</i>.

135
00:13:45.534 --> 00:13:47.661
I've seen that more times
than I can remember.

136
00:13:49.454 --> 00:13:52.559
- You can go. Tom. I'll call you later.
- Mr. Sugar.

137
00:13:52.583 --> 00:13:53.667
Thank you.

138
00:13:54.751 --> 00:13:55.878
- Shall we?
- Sure.

139
00:13:57.337 --> 00:14:00.340
So. you're a film buff?

140
00:14:00.841 --> 00:14:02.819
Buff? Buff is

141
00:14:02.843 --> 00:14:05.220
it's putting it lightly.
It's more like an addiction.

142
00:14:08.515 --> 00:14:11.059
That's not funny.
John. Not to me.

143
00:14:12.269 --> 00:14:14.980
When a client reaches out to you
directly. it's disrespectful.

144
00:14:15.606 --> 00:14:17.250
You're my business.

145
00:14:17.274 --> 00:14:20.837
Not to mention the fact that
you and I had an agreement

146
00:14:20.861 --> 00:14:22.988
that after Tokyo. you
would take a break.

147
00:14:24.114 --> 00:14:25.592
<i>A much-needed break.</i>

148
00:14:25.616 --> 00:14:27.743
I talked to Emily
Carpenter about you.

149
00:14:30.037 --> 00:14:33.123
Emily told me that you do
one thing and one thing only.

150
00:14:33.874 --> 00:14:34.958
You find the missing.

151
00:14:36.627 --> 00:14:38.712
for people who value discretion.

152
00:14:39.796 --> 00:14:41.298
like me.

153
00:14:42.216 --> 00:14:44.676
<i>- Ruby. it's Jonathan Siegel.
- I don't care who it is.</i>

154
00:14:46.720 --> 00:14:48.055
There's a girl missing.

155
00:14:49.765 --> 00:14:50.891
His granddaughter.

156
00:14:51.892 --> 00:14:55.663
She's 25 now. but she's
still a child to him.

157
00:14:55.687 --> 00:14:58.315
<i>Olivia has been
missing for two weeks.</i>

158
00:15:01.151 --> 00:15:05.322
<i>My son Bernard. he only told
me about it a few days ago.</i>

159
00:15:05.864 --> 00:15:09.552
<i>He thinks it's just another
one of her misadventures.</i>

160
00:15:09.576 --> 00:15:11.995
I had Tom's office prepare
what you requested.

161
00:15:16.208 --> 00:15:18.460
- That's her.
- Well. she's beautiful.

162
00:15:19.837 --> 00:15:22.464
She's done this
before? Disappeared?

163
00:15:23.173 --> 00:15:28.154
Yes. But that was because for
many years she had a drug problem

164
00:15:28.178 --> 00:15:31.991
and she'd often vanish for
days. weeks. months even.

165
00:15:32.015 --> 00:15:34.726
But this time it's different.
This time you're worried. Why?

166
00:15:35.769 --> 00:15:39.999
When Olivia would disappear
like that. she'd still call me.

167
00:15:40.023 --> 00:15:41.960
She'd always call me for money.

168
00:15:41.984 --> 00:15:43.253
which I gave her.

169
00:15:43.277 --> 00:15:45.421
And you haven't heard
from her? No calls. no...

170
00:15:45.445 --> 00:15:47.739
No. something
different this time.

171
00:15:48.240 --> 00:15:49.825
When was the last
time you saw Olivia?

172
00:15:51.952 --> 00:15:54.597
About a month ago. I
took her out to dinner.

173
00:15:54.621 --> 00:15:57.249
We celebrated two
years of her sobriety.

174
00:15:57.791 --> 00:16:00.377
She was very proud of
that. I was proud of her.

175
00:16:01.628 --> 00:16:05.525
There was something special
about her that night.

176
00:16:05.549 --> 00:16:07.009
Special? How so?

177
00:16:07.634 --> 00:16:13.056
She was passionate.
confident. eager. funny.

178
00:16:14.892 --> 00:16:17.996
It was so clear to me then.
she was finally on her way.

179
00:16:18.020 --> 00:16:19.396
On her way to what. sir?

180
00:16:21.148 --> 00:16:22.608
To becoming herself.

181
00:16:27.446 --> 00:16:29.031
I'm an old man. Sugar.

182
00:16:30.073 --> 00:16:32.451
and frankly I'm not that well.

183
00:16:33.577 --> 00:16:34.620
Bum ticker.

184
00:16:35.913 --> 00:16:38.165
I don't really give a damn
about anything anymore.

185
00:16:39.666 --> 00:16:41.752
except my granddaughter.

186
00:16:43.921 --> 00:16:47.382
I need you to find her. please.

187
00:16:49.718 --> 00:16:51.094
Well. that's his problem.

188
00:16:52.179 --> 00:16:53.847
It's not mine. and
it's not yours.

189
00:16:58.560 --> 00:16:59.728
We'll speak soon.

190
00:17:00.687 --> 00:17:01.915
<i>That's not funny. John.</i>

191
00:17:01.939 --> 00:17:04.525
<i>You need to call Thomas Kinzie
right now and set him straight.</i>

192
00:17:05.233 --> 00:17:06.233
<i>Ruby.</i>

193
00:17:07.736 --> 00:17:08.819
I can't do that.

194
00:17:10.571 --> 00:17:12.991
I can't do that. It's this girl.

195
00:17:19.790 --> 00:17:21.083
She reminds me of Djen.

196
00:17:25.170 --> 00:17:26.171
Yeah.

197
00:17:29.299 --> 00:17:30.467
I don't know what to say.

198
00:17:31.343 --> 00:17:32.886
She...

199
00:17:40.352 --> 00:17:43.414
God. You son of a bitch.

200
00:17:43.438 --> 00:17:44.624
What?

201
00:17:44.648 --> 00:17:46.543
You sure know how to
play me. don't you?

202
00:17:46.567 --> 00:17:49.254
- I ain't playing. Ruby. I ain't playing.
- Yeah.

203
00:17:49.278 --> 00:17:53.991
I saw her pictures. and
straightaway. it was Djen.

204
00:17:55.117 --> 00:17:56.719
Right. Well. you're
gonna need this stuff.

205
00:17:56.743 --> 00:17:58.555
It's a concealed carry permit.

206
00:17:58.579 --> 00:18:00.890
your renewed California
private investigator's license.

207
00:18:00.914 --> 00:18:01.975
- driver's license...
- Wait.

208
00:18:01.999 --> 00:18:05.043
Concealed carry permit.
why would I need that?

209
00:18:13.427 --> 00:18:15.446
Ruby. come on. You
know I don't like guns.

210
00:18:15.470 --> 00:18:17.490
Yes. I know. Come
on. It's just...

211
00:18:17.514 --> 00:18:18.992
Look. this isn't any
old gun. all right?

212
00:18:19.016 --> 00:18:21.703
This is the gun that Glenn
Ford used in <i>The Big Heat</i>.

213
00:18:21.727 --> 00:18:25.707
What do you mean the gun Glenn
Ford used in <i>The Big Heat</i>?

214
00:18:25.731 --> 00:18:27.625
What do you mean? Is
it. like. a replica?

215
00:18:27.649 --> 00:18:29.878
No. it's not a replica.

216
00:18:29.902 --> 00:18:31.486
Glenn Ford?

217
00:18:31.987 --> 00:18:33.506
Yeah. he used that gun.

218
00:18:33.530 --> 00:18:34.841
- Glenn Ford used this gun?
- I had...

219
00:18:34.865 --> 00:18:37.409
- Go on. Tell me.
- <i>Glenn Ford used that gun.</i>

220
00:18:38.493 --> 00:18:39.554
- Oh. my God.
- Yes.

221
00:18:39.578 --> 00:18:41.055
I bought that from
a private collector.

222
00:18:41.079 --> 00:18:43.790
I had it restored to perfect
working order just for you.

223
00:18:44.416 --> 00:18:46.853
- Why?
- I just feel more comfortable

224
00:18:46.877 --> 00:18:47.961
if you carried a gun.

225
00:18:48.462 --> 00:18:51.566
Plus. I figured this is the only
way I was gonna get you to do it.

226
00:18:51.590 --> 00:18:53.342
Who's playing who?

227
00:18:54.510 --> 00:18:58.156
- Wow. Well. thank you.
- There you go. You're welcome.

228
00:18:58.180 --> 00:19:01.308
- But. no. thank you.
- Nah. uh-uh. No.

229
00:19:02.476 --> 00:19:04.937
You can take all of this. but
you need to make some promises.

230
00:19:05.646 --> 00:19:07.081
Like what?

231
00:19:07.105 --> 00:19:09.125
Like you take this gun with you

232
00:19:09.149 --> 00:19:10.585
- right now.
- Fine.

233
00:19:10.609 --> 00:19:12.861
Okay. and then you make an
appointment with Dr. Vickers.

234
00:19:13.779 --> 00:19:15.465
Ruby. I feel...

235
00:19:15.489 --> 00:19:17.800
I'm in great health.
I feel perfect.

236
00:19:17.824 --> 00:19:21.221
Don't bullshit me.
John. I know you.

237
00:19:21.245 --> 00:19:24.331
- I don't need to see Dr. Vickers.
- Okay. John. how's your arm?

238
00:19:29.545 --> 00:19:30.546
Yeah.

239
00:19:31.880 --> 00:19:32.881
My arm's fine.

240
00:19:37.261 --> 00:19:38.261
All right.

241
00:19:38.846 --> 00:19:41.115
You can take the Siegel case.
But when it's done. you're done.

242
00:19:41.139 --> 00:19:42.224
Okay.

243
00:19:43.725 --> 00:19:45.185
Until I say otherwise.

244
00:19:46.311 --> 00:19:47.980
- All right. There you go.
- Okay.

245
00:19:49.231 --> 00:19:52.210
- I think you're forgetting something.
- No. that's pretty much everything.

246
00:19:52.234 --> 00:19:56.130
It's in your left hand. Show me.

247
00:19:56.154 --> 00:19:57.656
Thank you.

248
00:20:10.711 --> 00:20:12.397
I hate that you
drive this relic.

249
00:20:12.421 --> 00:20:15.007
Relic? This is a work of art.

250
00:20:22.681 --> 00:20:23.492
All right.

251
00:20:23.516 --> 00:20:24.766
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

252
00:20:25.350 --> 00:20:27.510
- You'll be at the Del Corazon. of course.
- Of course.

253
00:20:28.103 --> 00:20:29.622
You know. for what you
spend at that place.

254
00:20:29.646 --> 00:20:32.333
- we could get you a nice house.
- I like that place.

255
00:20:32.357 --> 00:20:34.878
I mean. it has maids who
clean my room twice a day.

256
00:20:34.902 --> 00:20:38.840
It has a concierge that takes care of
whatever I need. It has room service.

257
00:20:38.864 --> 00:20:41.885
No. you like that place because
the people who work there

258
00:20:41.909 --> 00:20:43.553
- make you feel like you belong.
- Really?

259
00:20:43.577 --> 00:20:45.412
- Yeah. like you're part of something.
- Wow.

260
00:20:46.288 --> 00:20:49.583
But it's an illusion.
Sugar. You need a home.

261
00:21:19.112 --> 00:21:20.089
Mr. Bascombe?

262
00:21:20.113 --> 00:21:22.258
Yes. Hey. call me Gary.

263
00:21:22.282 --> 00:21:24.594
- John Sugar.
- Hi. Yeah. Mr. Kinzie's office called.

264
00:21:24.618 --> 00:21:26.346
- said to let you in. So...
- Great.

265
00:21:26.370 --> 00:21:30.683
Hold on. Each tenant. do they
have their own parking space?

266
00:21:30.707 --> 00:21:32.209
Yeah. sure do. Some
of them have two.

267
00:21:32.918 --> 00:21:34.518
Could you show me
Miss Siegel's. please?

268
00:21:35.087 --> 00:21:36.421
Yeah. It's right this way.

269
00:21:40.175 --> 00:21:42.987
It has not moved
in. like. two weeks.

270
00:21:43.011 --> 00:21:46.699
How do you know? I assume you haven't
been watching the garage 24/7?

271
00:21:46.723 --> 00:21:50.203
Oh. no. All the tenants have
a gate opener in the car.

272
00:21:50.227 --> 00:21:51.996
and it records every
time they go in or out.

273
00:21:52.020 --> 00:21:55.566
There's a record of it on the security
computer thing in my office...

274
00:21:57.943 --> 00:22:00.255
By any chance. you have
a duplicate set of keys?

275
00:22:00.279 --> 00:22:02.215
For the cars? No.
just for the units.

276
00:22:02.239 --> 00:22:04.467
Okay. Can I see her place now?

277
00:22:04.491 --> 00:22:05.784
Yeah. This way.

278
00:22:08.537 --> 00:22:11.081
All righty. here we are.

279
00:22:12.833 --> 00:22:15.186
I didn't even know who she was.
Like. her family and everything.

280
00:22:15.210 --> 00:22:17.272
- Gary. thank you. I appreciate you.
- Yeah.

281
00:22:17.296 --> 00:22:19.298
I'll take it from here.
and I'll take the keys too.

282
00:22:20.215 --> 00:22:23.444
I've got keys for all the units.
You know. I'm the building manager.

283
00:22:23.468 --> 00:22:24.904
Yes. you are. But
it's a condominium.

284
00:22:24.928 --> 00:22:27.574
so all the keys are legal property
of the owner of the condominium.

285
00:22:27.598 --> 00:22:31.202
which is Jonathan Siegel. And as
Mr. Siegel's representative. I insist.

286
00:22:31.226 --> 00:22:32.287
Thank you.

287
00:22:32.311 --> 00:22:35.707
But what if something
happens? Like a leaky pipe?

288
00:22:35.731 --> 00:22:37.232
Just call me on this number.

289
00:22:38.233 --> 00:22:40.068
- Call you?
- Yeah. thank you.

290
00:22:40.777 --> 00:22:41.778
Welcome.

291
00:22:52.456 --> 00:22:53.457
<i>Nice place.</i>

292
00:22:56.752 --> 00:22:59.796
<i>She's a Siegel. so
of course it is.</i>

293
00:23:32.913 --> 00:23:36.142
What are you doing here?
Who the fuck are you?

294
00:23:36.166 --> 00:23:39.002
- I could ask you the same question.
- Kenny! Kenny!

295
00:23:40.963 --> 00:23:45.151
Whoa. Easy there. quick draw.

296
00:23:45.175 --> 00:23:47.821
I asked you a question.
motherfucker. Who the fuck are you?

297
00:23:47.845 --> 00:23:49.072
My name's John Sugar.

298
00:23:49.096 --> 00:23:51.866
I'm a private investigator licensed
by the State of California.

299
00:23:51.890 --> 00:23:55.203
- I have some identification in my pocket.
- Hey. keep your hands out of your pants.

300
00:23:55.227 --> 00:23:56.311
Okay.

301
00:24:01.233 --> 00:24:02.793
Sorry. I didn't
recognize you at first.

302
00:24:03.652 --> 00:24:04.712
Of course. Davy Siegel.

303
00:24:04.736 --> 00:24:05.821
David.

304
00:24:06.780 --> 00:24:08.007
It's not Davy anymore.

305
00:24:08.031 --> 00:24:09.717
You just shot that sequel. huh?

306
00:24:09.741 --> 00:24:11.719
To <i>The Boy in the Corner.</i>

307
00:24:11.743 --> 00:24:14.848
the one where you're the
same kid but all grown up?

308
00:24:14.872 --> 00:24:16.623
- Yeah.
- Good luck with that.

309
00:24:17.624 --> 00:24:20.210
Would you mind? Guns
make me nervous.

310
00:24:21.795 --> 00:24:22.796
Thank you.

311
00:24:23.881 --> 00:24:25.233
What are you doing here. man?

312
00:24:25.257 --> 00:24:26.609
I've been hired by
your grandfather

313
00:24:26.633 --> 00:24:28.570
to look into the
disappearance of your sister.

314
00:24:28.594 --> 00:24:30.446
If you wanna call him or
his attorney Mr. Kinzie.

315
00:24:30.470 --> 00:24:33.700
- they'll confirm what I just said.
- That's all right. I believe you.

316
00:24:33.724 --> 00:24:35.976
Good. So now we can get back
to our initial exchange.

317
00:24:37.811 --> 00:24:38.913
- Our what?
- Our... Well.

318
00:24:38.937 --> 00:24:40.456
I told you why I'm here.

319
00:24:40.480 --> 00:24:42.625
but you still haven't told
me what you're doing here.

320
00:24:42.649 --> 00:24:45.044
- My dad told me to come here.
- Really?

321
00:24:45.068 --> 00:24:47.839
I'm supposed to come here every
day to see if Olivia's back.

322
00:24:47.863 --> 00:24:50.157
- Where'd you get the keys?
- My dad.

323
00:24:51.283 --> 00:24:55.513
Bernie has a set of keys to the condo
that Jonathan bought your sister?

324
00:24:55.537 --> 00:24:57.807
Half-sister. But. yeah.

325
00:24:57.831 --> 00:25:00.083
Why didn't you just ring
or knock on the door?

326
00:25:04.087 --> 00:25:06.399
- What?
- Well. you're looking for Olivia. right?

327
00:25:06.423 --> 00:25:09.944
I mean. she could still be here.
but you just assume that she wasn't.

328
00:25:09.968 --> 00:25:11.448
Yeah. she could have
been passed out.

329
00:25:11.845 --> 00:25:14.126
I don't know how much you know
about Olivia but. you know.

330
00:25:14.473 --> 00:25:16.016
once a junkie. always a junkie.

331
00:25:18.936 --> 00:25:21.956
- You're a terrible liar. Davy.
- David.

332
00:25:21.980 --> 00:25:23.398
Maybe the worst liar ever.

333
00:25:25.859 --> 00:25:27.003
Well. Olivia's not here.

334
00:25:27.027 --> 00:25:28.111
Yeah. I figured.

335
00:25:29.029 --> 00:25:31.573
So there's no reason for you
to be here either. is there?

336
00:25:37.079 --> 00:25:38.056
Nice suit.

337
00:25:38.080 --> 00:25:39.248
Night. Kenny.

338
00:25:40.249 --> 00:25:41.625
It's always nice to meet a fan.

339
00:25:43.460 --> 00:25:44.461
That was good.

340
00:25:44.962 --> 00:25:46.672
<i>Well. that was interesting.</i>

341
00:25:47.172 --> 00:25:48.215
<i>Scared little boy.</i>

342
00:25:49.758 --> 00:25:51.176
{\an8}<i>Scared of what. I wonder?</i>

343
00:25:52.135 --> 00:25:53.136
<i>Scared of who?</i>

344
00:26:00.227 --> 00:26:01.395
<i>Olivia's mom.</i>

345
00:26:01.979 --> 00:26:03.957
<i>Yeah. I guess I see it.</i>

346
00:26:03.981 --> 00:26:05.399
<i>It's the eyes.</i>

347
00:26:06.900 --> 00:26:08.068
Rachel Kaye.

348
00:26:08.652 --> 00:26:10.112
<i>Same sadness there.</i>

349
00:26:40.184 --> 00:26:41.619
<i>I recognize the blonde.</i>

350
00:26:41.643 --> 00:26:42.871
<i>Melanie Matthews.</i>

351
00:26:42.895 --> 00:26:46.356
<i>Used to be Olivia's stepmom
and a big rock star too.</i>

352
00:26:46.857 --> 00:26:48.150
<i>But this is recent.</i>

353
00:26:53.071 --> 00:26:54.111
<i>Maybe she knows something.</i>

354
00:26:56.783 --> 00:26:58.076
<i>Step-Hi Lounge.</i>

355
00:26:59.036 --> 00:27:02.080
<i>Melanie wasn't at home. so the bar from
the picture seems like my next stop.</i>

356
00:27:04.208 --> 00:27:05.209
<i>I know the place.</i>

357
00:27:21.266 --> 00:27:22.386
What's your name. my friend?

358
00:27:23.810 --> 00:27:26.271
- Carl.
- Carl. John.

359
00:27:26.855 --> 00:27:29.191
It's nice to meet
you. Carl. His name?

360
00:27:29.900 --> 00:27:31.026
- That's Wiley.
- Can I...

361
00:27:31.818 --> 00:27:34.238
- Yeah.
- Hey. Hey. Wiley.

362
00:27:36.073 --> 00:27:37.991
Hey. Carl. would
you do me a favor?

363
00:27:38.492 --> 00:27:39.844
Could you watch my car?

364
00:27:39.868 --> 00:27:42.788
I'll pay you. like. a
couple hundred bucks.

365
00:27:43.330 --> 00:27:45.010
You don't have to do
anything. You just...

366
00:27:48.627 --> 00:27:52.524
You know. anyone tries to steal it
or. hell. anyone gets too close to it.

367
00:27:52.548 --> 00:27:54.967
all you gotta do...
Here's a telephone.

368
00:27:56.051 --> 00:27:57.678
You just call me at this number.

369
00:27:59.221 --> 00:28:00.532
Hundred bucks.

370
00:28:00.556 --> 00:28:03.267
When I get back. I'll give you
the other half. Sound good?

371
00:28:03.767 --> 00:28:06.270
- Yeah. Sounds real good.
- Okay. Cool.

372
00:28:08.188 --> 00:28:10.315
- Hey. Wiley.
- He's friendly.

373
00:28:11.984 --> 00:28:13.235
You're a good man. Carl.

374
00:28:24.204 --> 00:28:26.206
<i>We are golden.</i>

375
00:28:27.624 --> 00:28:30.603
<i>And I'm out here on the road</i>

376
00:28:30.627 --> 00:28:33.714
<i>I feel just like
a rolling stone.</i>

377
00:28:35.382 --> 00:28:41.382
<i>Into the highways of
the night I roll alone.</i>

378
00:28:44.057 --> 00:28:46.494
<i>At first. I was gonna
call it a coincidence.</i>

379
00:28:46.518 --> 00:28:48.788
<i>finding Olivia's
mystery woman so easily.</i>

380
00:28:48.812 --> 00:28:52.274
<i>But something tells me she could
have been found here most anytime.</i>

381
00:28:52.816 --> 00:28:54.943
- Get you something?
- Whatever she's drinking.

382
00:28:55.569 --> 00:28:58.298
Willett Distillery
single-barrel bourbon. sir.

383
00:28:58.322 --> 00:29:00.758
That's gonna be $100 a shot.

384
00:29:00.782 --> 00:29:03.011
Neat. Water back. I'd
like to pay for hers too.

385
00:29:03.035 --> 00:29:07.247
That's nice of you. man. but she does
not like dudes buying her drinks.

386
00:29:07.789 --> 00:29:08.874
I respect that.

387
00:29:10.083 --> 00:29:11.084
Thank you.

388
00:29:14.922 --> 00:29:16.173
That's very good.

389
00:29:18.050 --> 00:29:21.929
I usually drink scotch. but
this could change things.

390
00:29:22.471 --> 00:29:23.722
You ever have rye?

391
00:29:25.015 --> 00:29:28.953
Rye falls somewhere in between
that beautiful whiskey sweet spot.

392
00:29:28.977 --> 00:29:31.623
No. I'd hear cowboys
order it in westerns.

393
00:29:31.647 --> 00:29:34.000
You know. "Barkeep.
give me a shot of rye."

394
00:29:34.024 --> 00:29:35.776
But I never thought
to actually try it.

395
00:29:45.869 --> 00:29:47.514
- Melanie.
- John.

396
00:29:47.538 --> 00:29:49.039
Hey. Melanie.

397
00:29:50.999 --> 00:29:52.000
You wanna get drunk?

398
00:29:54.211 --> 00:29:55.879
I think the lady
needs a fresh one.

399
00:29:58.090 --> 00:30:02.362
You matched me drink for drink. but I'm
sloshed. and you're stone-cold sober.

400
00:30:02.386 --> 00:30:06.723
Yeah. I have a
strange metabolism.

401
00:30:07.224 --> 00:30:12.247
My body. it processes alcohol at a
rate 50 times faster than normal.

402
00:30:12.271 --> 00:30:15.774
I mean. I could drink that. this.
every drink in this establishment.

403
00:30:16.358 --> 00:30:19.087
- and I still wouldn't get drunk.
- That sounds expensive.

404
00:30:19.111 --> 00:30:20.112
It can be.

405
00:30:22.364 --> 00:30:23.740
Why drink?

406
00:30:25.367 --> 00:30:27.452
I think I like
the romance of it.

407
00:30:29.037 --> 00:30:30.372
Yeah.

408
00:30:31.623 --> 00:30:33.125
I suppose I get that
from the movies.

409
00:30:34.585 --> 00:30:35.586
I love the movies.

410
00:30:36.128 --> 00:30:37.254
I like sci-fi.

411
00:30:37.754 --> 00:30:38.940
You like sci-fi?

412
00:30:38.964 --> 00:30:41.276
Any particular
titles that you have?

413
00:30:41.300 --> 00:30:44.279
Like. a go-to sci-fi film...

414
00:30:44.303 --> 00:30:45.971
How many questions?

415
00:30:48.473 --> 00:30:50.493
Hold on. I gotta
figure this out. Okay.

416
00:30:50.517 --> 00:30:54.080
You're not an asshole
or a douche or a sleaze.

417
00:30:54.104 --> 00:30:55.707
- No. Most...
- How do you know? We just met.

418
00:30:55.731 --> 00:30:58.334
Most men fall into those
categories. I know. I know.

419
00:30:58.358 --> 00:30:59.502
You don't.

420
00:30:59.526 --> 00:31:04.907
but there's more to
you than meets the eye.

421
00:31:05.782 --> 00:31:10.412
You have secrets. and
you keep things hidden.

422
00:31:10.913 --> 00:31:14.517
Just things you only
share with a trusted few.

423
00:31:14.541 --> 00:31:19.522
And gaining that
trust. that's not easy.

424
00:31:19.546 --> 00:31:20.923
Wow.

425
00:31:30.807 --> 00:31:32.351
Do you wanna take me home?

426
00:31:34.061 --> 00:31:35.103
It's okay.

427
00:31:38.607 --> 00:31:40.609
Hey. Carl. Thank you.

428
00:31:43.153 --> 00:31:45.590
Thanks for remembering
my name. Mr. Sugar.

429
00:31:45.614 --> 00:31:47.741
- John.
- John.

430
00:31:49.660 --> 00:31:51.453
Okay. Just give me one second.

431
00:31:52.829 --> 00:31:53.890
Thank you.

432
00:31:53.914 --> 00:31:55.934
Wiley. thank you. Thank you.

433
00:31:55.958 --> 00:31:58.335
- He likes you.
- I like him too.

434
00:31:59.837 --> 00:32:02.548
As promised. Thank you. sir.

435
00:32:03.215 --> 00:32:04.484
- Thank you. sir.
- Uh-huh.

436
00:32:04.508 --> 00:32:05.568
Mr. Su... John.

437
00:32:05.592 --> 00:32:07.177
John. John.

438
00:32:07.761 --> 00:32:09.322
Cool. Here's your...

439
00:32:09.346 --> 00:32:10.848
You know what? Keep that.

440
00:32:11.390 --> 00:32:14.726
Right. And I want you to find somewhere
decent for you and Wiley to sleep tonight.

441
00:32:16.061 --> 00:32:17.061
Yeah?

442
00:32:17.479 --> 00:32:19.207
- Yeah.
- Okay.

443
00:32:19.231 --> 00:32:20.399
You got any family. Carl?

444
00:32:23.485 --> 00:32:26.113
I got a sister in Milwaukee.

445
00:32:26.613 --> 00:32:29.342
- Uh-huh. What's her name?
- Sophie.

446
00:32:29.366 --> 00:32:30.927
- Sophie?
- Yeah.

447
00:32:30.951 --> 00:32:33.996
Sophie. Does she know
what's going on with you?

448
00:32:39.626 --> 00:32:43.314
She... Well...

449
00:32:43.338 --> 00:32:46.425
Carl. I want you to use that
phone and call Sophie tonight.

450
00:32:47.176 --> 00:32:49.112
Call her and ask
her if you can stay.

451
00:32:49.136 --> 00:32:53.515
Okay? Just tell her what's happened.
Don't let pride get in the way.

452
00:32:54.224 --> 00:32:55.493
Just 'cause you're
living on the streets.

453
00:32:55.517 --> 00:32:57.579
it doesn't make you any less
human than the rest of us.

454
00:32:57.603 --> 00:32:59.403
What's happened to you
could happen to anyone.

455
00:33:00.814 --> 00:33:02.574
Can you do that? Can
you call Sophie tonight?

456
00:33:04.026 --> 00:33:05.152
- Uh-huh.
- Yeah.

457
00:33:05.944 --> 00:33:07.029
You call her tonight.

458
00:33:07.529 --> 00:33:10.741
And you call me tomorrow. I'll get
you a ticket to Milwaukee. okay?

459
00:33:12.701 --> 00:33:15.537
- I got Wiley. so...
- We'll get him on as a service dog.

460
00:33:16.163 --> 00:33:20.375
Not a problem. I'll get him a
ticket too. I promise. Deal?

461
00:33:24.046 --> 00:33:25.899
Okay. Okay. all right.

462
00:33:25.923 --> 00:33:27.925
- Hey.
- Hey. it's okay. Come here.

463
00:33:28.592 --> 00:33:30.195
- Come here. boy.
- Come on back in. You're okay.

464
00:33:30.219 --> 00:33:32.339
- We're going to Milwaukee.
- Yeah. you're going home.

465
00:33:32.888 --> 00:33:34.032
We'll talk tomorrow?

466
00:33:34.056 --> 00:33:35.976
- I'll call you tomorrow. sir.
- All right. Okay.

467
00:33:36.683 --> 00:33:38.852
Hey. thank you.

468
00:33:43.232 --> 00:33:44.233
Excuse me.

469
00:33:45.150 --> 00:33:46.693
I think he liked you.

470
00:33:47.736 --> 00:33:48.737
He called you sugar.

471
00:33:50.280 --> 00:33:51.281
No. that's my name.

472
00:33:51.865 --> 00:33:53.158
Your name is John Sugar?

473
00:33:53.909 --> 00:33:55.744
Yeah. John Sugar.

474
00:33:56.870 --> 00:33:58.997
Okay. I'm not gonna forget that.

475
00:34:03.669 --> 00:34:05.462
<i>When's your
birthday. John Sugar?</i>

476
00:34:06.255 --> 00:34:07.398
<i>September 2nd.</i>

477
00:34:07.422 --> 00:34:09.442
<i>Virgo? I knew it.</i>

478
00:34:09.466 --> 00:34:12.403
<i>I love Virgo. Honest.
loyal and kind.</i>

479
00:34:12.427 --> 00:34:15.448
<i>When you meet someone
unlike you. you know it.</i>

480
00:34:15.472 --> 00:34:17.599
<i>- You are who you are.
- Really?</i>

481
00:34:18.475 --> 00:34:19.536
<i>I knew it.</i>

482
00:34:19.560 --> 00:34:22.603
<i>But. you know. deep
down. you're lonely.</i>

483
00:34:25.274 --> 00:34:30.152
You don't have a wife
or kids or a home.

484
00:34:30.821 --> 00:34:32.906
You choose to be alone.

485
00:34:36.534 --> 00:34:38.786
But there's hope
for you. John Sugar.

486
00:34:40.539 --> 00:34:41.540
Is there?

487
00:34:52.634 --> 00:34:54.261
- My home.
- Uh-huh.

488
00:34:54.803 --> 00:34:56.280
